{
  "text": "Previously, we reported a significant increase in number of iNKT cells sequestered in the liver following BDL [CITATION_1] . Experiments were undertaken to explore the potential role of Kupffer cells and the mechanism(s) involved. Mice were rendered Kupffer cell-deficient prior to BDL by the administration of Cl 2 MDP-L; control mice received PBS. At 18 hours post-BDL, the animals were euthanized, NPCs collected, and iNKT cells quantified and characterized.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "5271221"
